"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-arts-entertainment-tv-news-olympics-bbc-clare-balding-watch-paris-b2590925.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Broadcaster was thrown an embarrassing curveball live on-air  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 383, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  Clare Baldingfound herself at the centre of an \\\"awkward\\\"BBCblunder while presenting theOlympicscoverage.\", \"from\": 384, \"to\": 512, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 408, \"end\": 413, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clare_GAA\", \"score\": 0.9997149819308252, \"rank\": 0.0002849364318709097, \"text\": \"Clare\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clare_GAA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clare_GAA\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Days afterfinding herself embroiled in a classism debate, the sports broadcaster was introducing viewers to the 200m breaststroke final when the BBC prematurely revealed the winner of the race as she was talking.\", \"from\": 514, \"to\": 726, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 659, \"end\": 662, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.991978653242654, \"rank\": 0.004322898422138201, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Balding was speaking to the camera when the US national anthem could be heard playing over the speakers, and she told viewers: \\\"The US national anthem is going out behind us for a race we are going to show you now - the 200m breaststroke final.\\\"\", \"from\": 728, \"to\": 973, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 772, \"end\": 790, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Star-Spangled_Banner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"US national anthem\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Star-Spangled_Banner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Star-Spangled_Banner\"}, {\"begin\": 860, \"end\": 878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Star-Spangled_Banner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"US national anthem\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Star-Spangled_Banner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Star-Spangled_Banner\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She then added: \\\"So do not listen to that 'cause otherwise it'll give away the...\\\" - at which point, the cameras revealed that Kate Douglas had won the gold medal.\", \"from\": 975, \"to\": 1138, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1102, \"end\": 1106, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\", \"score\": 0.9999943380106507, \"rank\": 5.662021317387427e-06, \"text\": \"Kate\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\"}, {\"begin\": 1107, \"end\": 1114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_O._Douglas\", \"score\": 0.9969508118150192, \"rank\": 0.0030498098719955453, \"text\": \"Douglas\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_O._Douglas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_O._Douglas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Balding defeatedly then announced: \\\"OK, Kate Douglas winning the 200m breaststroke!\\\"\", \"from\": 1140, \"to\": 1224, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1180, \"end\": 1184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\", \"score\": 0.9999943380106507, \"rank\": 5.662021317387427e-06, \"text\": \"Kate\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\"}, {\"begin\": 1185, \"end\": 1192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_O._Douglas\", \"score\": 0.9969508118150192, \"rank\": 0.0030498098719955453, \"text\": \"Douglas\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_O._Douglas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_O._Douglas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TV criticScott Bryanbranded the moment \\\"awkward\\\" on social media, writing: \\\"BBC accidentally showing us who won a swimming race before showing us the swimming race is very BBC Olympics.\\\"\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1412, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1302, \"end\": 1305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.991978653242654, \"rank\": 0.004322898422138201, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}, {\"begin\": 1398, \"end\": 1401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.991978653242654, \"rank\": 0.004322898422138201, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One viewer called it :unfortunate timing\\\", while another jokingly compared it to Christopher Nolan's timebending filmTenet, posting: \\\"It's like the filmTenet: between BBC One and the Red Button, we are seeing things out of order before they happen depending on which way round we see it.\\\"\", \"from\": 1414, \"to\": 1702, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1495, \"end\": 1512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christopher_Nolan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6019210069673518e-27, \"text\": \"Christopher Nolan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christopher_Nolan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christopher_Nolan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, one person threw their support on Balding, calling it \\\"a slightly funny & endearing broadcasting mistake that's actually handled quite well in the moment\\\".\", \"from\": 1704, \"to\": 1870, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier this week, unimpressed BBC viewers suggested Balding appeared \\\"incredulous\\\" that noOlympianshad visited the school of gold medallistRebecca Adlingtongrowing up.\", \"from\": 1872, \"to\": 2040, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1903, \"end\": 1906, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.991978653242654, \"rank\": 0.004322898422138201, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This led some to call out the comment for revealing Balding's \\\"class privilege\\\".\", \"from\": 2042, \"to\": 2122, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The commenta rrived after Mark Foster, a former Olympian swimmer and flag-bearer at the BeijingOlympicsin 2008, reflected on his inspiration as he shared that Duncan Goodhew had visited his swimming club when he was ten years old, moving him to try to follow in his footsteps.\", \"from\": 2124, \"to\": 2400, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2150, \"end\": 2161, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Foster_the_People\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9654388715628728e-19, \"text\": \"Mark Foster\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Foster_the_People\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Foster_the_People\"}, {\"begin\": 2172, \"end\": 2180, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.99999998945691, \"rank\": 1.0543117790947182e-08, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resour